:<font size="15">כּוּשׁ</font></div>

===Pronunciation===
כּוּשׁ / kûsh / koosh

===Etymology===
Probably of foreign origin; 

===Proper noun===
'''כּוּשׁ'''

# Cush (or Ethiopia), the name of a son of Ham, and of his territory; also of an Israelite: - Chush, Cush, [[Ethiopia]].

